            <Field key="sec_vacancy"><Value>Housing and Finance Coach - Southampton - CGL 3564

   Service:
   Southampton Drug and Alcohol Recovery Service (DARS)
   Salary:
   £19,024 - £22,371 per annum pro rat
   Hours:
   15 per week
   Closing Date:
   Thursday, 4 July 2019 - 11:45pm
   Job Reference:
   CGL3564

   Change Grow Live Southampton is an Integrated Drug and Alcohol Recovery Service working with people within the city. We provide a broad range of services - including open access to a range of evidence-based interventions and treatments for adults experiencing problems with drugs, or drugs and alcohol, whilst promoting a focus on harm reduction, recovery and independence.

   Our dedicated local team are passionate about believing in the capacity of people to make changes and if you share this value our Change Coach roles may be of interest to you.

   We are looking for a team of passionate and talented individuals to join our team delivering a range of innovative Coaching roles, designed to inspire and support individuals in their recovery and to support self-belief, wellbeing and integration with local communities.

   These roles provide exciting opportunities to contribute to the development and success of the Change Grow Live service as it enters a new phase of delivery having been recently recommissioned in the city. Individuals will need to be caring, bold, open-minded and highly motivated in order to meet the expectations of these challenging roles, but training and governance are in place to provide support.

   We currently have part time vacancies for the following roles:

   Cooking and Growing Coach - 15 hours per week

   Holistic Therapies Coach - 15 hours per week

   Housing and Finance Coach - 15hours per week

   Education, Training and Employment Coach - 22.5 hours per week

   Terms for roles differ and it is recommended that you review the individual Job Descriptions for the posts in which you have an interest.

   Change Grow Live are committed to creating an inclusive environment, which celebrates difference and allows our staff and service users to flourish. We recruit the very best staff from a wide range of backgrounds, ensuring service users benefit from our diverse skills and expertise. We always work to the principles of fairness and equality of opportunity in all our recruitment processes.

   We also expect an assertive approach to ensuring the safety and well-being of all children, young people and adults, and applicants to these posts will need to demonstrate an understanding of and commitment to best safeguarding practice.

   Please note, if you have not heard from us within three weeks of the closing date, your application has not been shortlisted on this occasion.

   The successful candidate will be required to undergo a basic DBS check.

   To apply for this position, please download and complete the form on this page.

Apply for this position

   First download and fill in the following application form.
